This correspondence has been published in 1906 or 1907—no, 1906, after all—by Ferz Bretwit’s widow—I may even have a copy of it somewhere among my books. Moreover, this is not a holograph but an apograph, made by a scribe for the printers—you will note that both mayors write the same hand.”

“How interesting,” said Gradus noting it.

“Naturally I appreciate the kind thought behind it,” said Bretwit.

“We were sure you would,” said pleased Gradus.

